HSBC Favors Brazil Inflation Bonds for Investors, Folha Reports

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-09-17T15:23:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/hsbc-favors-brazil-inflation-bonds-for-investors-folha-reports.html
HSBC Global Asset Management favors
 Brazil  inflation bonds for investors seeking protection against
inflation,  Folha de S.Paulo  reported, citing  Philip Poole , HSBC
global head of investment strategy.  The risks of higher inflation have increased in Brazil and
there is concern over how the nation’s central bank may react,
the newspaper said, citing Poole.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in São Paulo at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Helder Marinho at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net . 